                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d68">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Officers of the United States</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-11-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 25, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Gentlemen</hi>: I have to inform you that, in view of the
                    convention signed November 17, 1905, between Japan and Korea, by which Japan
                    becomes the medium for conducting the foreign relations of Korea, the American
                    legation at Seoul has been withdrawn, and that the representation of the United
                    States in diplomatic matters effecting American rights of treaty, persons, and
                    property in Korea will hereafter be dealt with through the channel of the
                    Japanese foreign office.</p>
                <p>I am etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Elihu Root.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
